Responsibilities : 
OKTA administration- including patching and platform management, user administration and management 
Implementing and supporting OKTA multi-factor authentication and SSO solution. 
Develop and implement processes and procedures to ensure that is able to meet its customers' expectations and deliver quality services within specified Service Level Agreements (SLAs) and contractual obligations. 
Ensure that all Service Management processes are followed, and all incidents and requests are addressed within the required time to adhere to published SLAs. 
Coordinate escalations and collaborate with internal technology teams to ensure timely resolution of issues. 
Perform system maintenance and maintain current documentation. 
Propose process and technical improvements to enhance the customer's environment and experience. 
Maintain system integrations between LDAP directory, identity management system, and Third-Party systems. 
Run reporting of usage statistics. 
Create user notifications informing end users of enrollment on the server. 
Maintain the application by applying patches and troubleshooting issues and import of licenses Create logical separations of duties for users in the environment. 
Provision & De-Provision users within the Tool. 
